{"tid":1779521,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"新聞自由 2019年中國拉左起碼48 位記者 達全球之冠","createTime":"2019-12-11T17:26:47.000Z","updateTime":"2019-12-12T15:29:13.000Z","uid":165683,"like":6,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":6,"replies":[{"pid":"2d6ab49b21d7722a9c417d7011c81a43b829d200","tid":1779521,"uid":165683,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-12-11T17:26:47.000Z","msg":"(Reuters) - China imprisoned at least 48 journalists in 2019, more than any other country, displacing Turkey as the most oppressive place for the profession, a report by the Committee to Protect Journalists report said on Wednesday.<br />\n<br />\nFILE PHOTO: Journalists take pictures outside the venue of a summit at the Belt and Road Forum in Beijing, China, May 15, 2017. REUTERS/Thomas Peter<br />\nAt least 250 journalists were imprisoned worldwide this year, according to the report, which the committee compiles annually. The total last year was 255, said the report by the New York-based CPJ.<br />\n<br />\nChina&rsquo;s total rose by one since last year. The report noted that &ldquo;the number has steadily increased since President Xi Jinping consolidated political control of the country.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nwww.reut.rs/2E8zjne<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Reuters/status/1204813833791057921\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FReuters%2Fstatus%2F1204813833791057921&d=WPWOQTheSiAT%2FB2p9vAnABD7%2Fo0bOSfVmdYqJtNqH20%3D&h=204c9ebd\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FReuters%2Fstatus%2F1204813833791057921&h=a4c207d6\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://twitter.com/Reuters/status/1204813833791057921</a>"},{"pid":"78f902937707fd41863c71ef6c509ee424670fb5","tid":1779521,"uid":334806,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-12-11T17:27:28.000Z","msg":"支那又贏<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9208fbf40375d17f099cf60998d44d069f766fe1","tid":1779521,"uid":1